===Etymology===
From {{etyl|hi}} {{term|रुपीया|tr=rupīyā|lang=hi|sc=Deva}}, variant of {{term|रुपया|lang=hi|tr=rupayā|sc=Deva}}
: < from {{etyl|ur}} {{term|رپيا|lang=ur|sc=ur-Arab|tr=rupayā}}, coined by [[w:Mughal Empire|Mughal emperor]] [[w:Sher Shah Suri|Sher Shah Suri]] (1540–45)
:: < from {{etyl|sa}} {{term|रूप्यकं|lang=sa|sc=Deva|tr=rūpyakam||[[silver]] [[coin]]}}
::: < from {{etyl|sa}} {{term|रूप्य|lang=sa|sc=Deva|tr=rūpya||[[wrought]] silver}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The common name for the [[monetary]] [[currency|currencies]] used in modern [[India]], [[Pakistan]], [[Nepal]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Seychelles]], [[Hyrule]], or [[Mauritius]].
# A silver coin, circulating in [[India]] 16th–20th centuries, weighing 170–180&nbsp;[[troy grain]]s (180&nbsp;troy grains from 1833) or one [[tola]].

